cope=\"row\"| \"To My Youth\"<br>{{small|({{lang|ja|\u79c1\u306e\u601d\u6625\u671f\u3078}})}}\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Workaholic\"<br>{{small|({{lang|ko|\uc6cc\ucee4\ud640\ub9ad}})}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Two Five''\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Zanybros\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"25\"\n|-\n| 2020\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Love\"\n| {{TBA}}\n|}\n\n== Television Appearance ==\n=== Variety Shows ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!style=\"width: 5%|Year\n!style=\"width: 20%|Title\n!style=\"width: 10%|Network\n!style=\"width: 10%|Role\n!style=\"width: 30%|Notes/ Ref.\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Superstar K 6]]''\n|[[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n|Contestant\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://enter.etoday.co.kr/view/news_view.php?varAtcId=19838|title=\u2018\uc288\ud37c\uc2a4\ud0c0K6\u2019 \ubcfc\ube68\uac04 \uc0ac\ucd98\uae30, \uacbd\ubd81 \uc601\uc8fc \ucd9c\uc2e0 \uc2e4\ub825\ud30c...\uc774\uc2b9\ucca0 \u201c\uae30\ud2b9\ud558\ub2e4\u201d|date=2014-08-29|publisher=EToday|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[My Little Television]]''\n|[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|Cast\n|On Episode 84 & 85<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/198252|title=\ubcfc\ube68\uac04\uc0ac\ucd98\uae30 \ud45c '\ubaa8\ub2dd\ucf5c' \ub300\uacf5\uac1c! {{!}} MBC \uc5f0\uc608 \uc2a4\ud3ec\uce20|date=2017-02-03|publisher=Enews IMBC |language=ko}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Bolbbalgan4}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.shofar-music.com/}}\n\n{{Golden Disk Awards for New Artist of the Year}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2016]]\n[[Category:South Korean girl groups]]\n[[Category:2016 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:South Korean musical duos]]\n[[Category:Korean Music Award winners]]\n[[Category:Melon Music Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean band}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Bolbbalgan4\n| background      = group_or_band\n| image           = 180306 Bolbbalgan4 at a fansinging (4).jpg\n| caption         = Bolbbalgan4 in March 2018 <br />Woo Ji-yoon (left) and [[Ahn Ji-young]] (right)\n| alias           = BOL4<ref name=itunes>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/bol4/1188975595|title=BOL4 on Apple Music|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref><br />Blushing Youth\n| origin          = [[Yeongju]], [[North Gyeongsang Province|Gyeongsang]], South Korea\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Contemporary folk music|folk rock]]|[[Rhythm & Blues]]|[[Indie pop]]}}\n| years_active    = 2016\u2013present\n| label           = {{hlist|Shofar Music|[[King Records (Japan)|King Records]]}}\n| website         = * {{url|www.shofar-music.com/}}\n* {{url|https://bol4.jp/}}\n| current_members = \n* [[Ahn Ji-young]]\n| former_members   = * Woo Ji-yoon\n}}\n'''Bolbbalgan4''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ubcfc\ube68\uac04 \uc0ac\ucd98\uae30}}, also known as '''BOL4'''<ref name=itunes /> or '''Blushing Youth''' or '''Blushing Puberty''', pronounced '''Bolbbalgan Sachungi''') is a South Korean musical act formed by Shofar Music in 2016. They appeared on [[Superstar K6]] in 2014 before signing a contract with their current agency. BOL4 was originally a duo consisting of [[Ahn Ji-young]] and [[Woo Ji-yoon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sisunnews.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=42324|title=\ubcfc\ube68\uac04 \uc0ac\ucd98\uae30', \uc288\uc2a4\ucf006 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \uc774\ud6c4\ub85c \"\uc601\uc8fc \uc2dc\uc7a5\uacfc \ud1b5\ud654\ud588\ub2e4|publisher=Sisun News|language=ko|date=2016-09-21}}</ref> They debuted with the single \"Fight Day\" from the mini-album ''Red Ickle'' on April 22, 2016. The meaning of \uc0ac\ucd98\uae30(\u601d\u6625\u671f) is \"puberty\" in English. In Korean, the pronunciation of \uc0ac(\u601d) is the same as \uc0ac(\u56db=4), so the group name is sometimes shortened to '''Bol4'''. \n\nThe duo went on a temporary hiatus due to Ahn's music classes requirements in the first half of 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.insight.co.kr/news/144796|title=\u2018\ud559\uc0ac \uacbd\uace0 \uc704\uae30\u2019 \uc640 \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc804\uba74 \uc911\ub2e8\ud558\uace0 \u2018\ub300\ud559\uc0dd\u2019\uc73c\ub85c \ub3cc\uc544\uac04 \ubcfc\ube68\uac04\uc0ac\ucd98\uae30|publisher=Insight|date=2018-03-14|language=ko}}</ref> Bolbbalgan4 signed with [[King Records (Japan)|King Records]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://entertain.v.daum.net/v/20190404074233599|title=\ubcfc\ube68\uac04\uc0ac\ucd98\uae30, 6\uc6d4 \uc77c\ubcf8 \uc815\uc2dd \ub370\ubdd4..'\uc6b0\uc8fc\ub97c \uc904\uac8c' \u65e5 \ubc84\uc804 \ucd9c\uc2dc [\uacf5\uc2dd]|publisher=Daum|date=2019-04-04|language=ko}}</ref> and debuted in Japan on June 5, 2019, with the mini-album ''Red Planet (Japan Edition)''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.dwango.jp/music/37719-1905|title=\u8d64\u982c\u601d\u6625\u671f\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fcAL\u3088\u308a\u300e\u5b87\u5b99\u3092\u3042\u3052\u308b\u300fMV\u30d5\u30eb\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\u304c\u516c\u958b|publisher=Dwango News|language=ja|date=2019-05-22}}</ref><ref name=\"debutshowcase\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/d_news/detail/75822/2|title=\u97d3\u56fd\u30b7\u30c6\u30a3\u30dd\u30c3\u30d7\u306e\u5927\u672c\u547d\u30fb\u8d64\u982c\u601d\u6625\u671f\u3001\u300c\u5b87\u5b99\u3092\u3042\u3052\u308b\u300dMV\u516c\u958b\uff06\u5148\u884c\u914d\u4fe1\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8|publisher=Billboard Japan|language=ja|date=2019-05-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2136101/amp/|title=\u97d3\u56fd\u306e\u30b9\u30c8\u30ea\u30fc\u30df\u30f3\u30b0\u5973\u738b\u30fb\u8d64\u982c\u601d\u6625\u671f\u3001\u30b5\u30de\u30bd\u30cb\u51fa\u6f14|publisher=Oricon News|language=ja|date=2019-05-23}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 2020, Shofar Music announced that Woo Ji-yoon had left the duo, with Ahn Ji-young to continue promoting as Bolbbalgan4.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.donga.com/article/all/20200402/100469171/1|title=[\uc804\ubb38] \ubcfc\ube68\uac04 \uc0ac\ucd98\uae30 \uce21 \u201c\uc9c0\uc724 \ud0c8\ud1f4\u21921\uc778 \uccb4\uc81c\ub85c 5\uc6d4 \uc0c8\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ud45c\u201d (\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5)|publisher=Sports DongA|language=Korean|date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Formation==\nJiyoung and Jiyoon were both raised in [[Yeongju|Yeongju city]], [[North Gyeongsang Province|Gyeongsang]], and were classmates. They had previously competed SuperStarK6 in 2018. Since they were young they had dreamed of becoming singers. The name of their duo was built on the grounds that they wanted to make the kind of pure, honest music that can only be found in adolescence. Jiyoon portrays the \"blushing\" part of the name because she is often shy, while Jiyoung portrays \"youth\" because she acts like an adolescent girl.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://enews24.interest.me/news/article.asp?nsID=1101972|title=\uc62c\ub4dc\uc2a4\ucfe8' \ubcfc\ube68\uac04 \uc0ac\ucd98\uae30 \"\uc74c\uc6d0\ucc28\ud2b8 \uc5ed\uc8fc\ud589 \uc2e0\uae30\ud574\" \ubc1c\ub784 \uc785\ub2f4 '\ub208\uae38|publisher=ENews24|language=Korean|date=2016-09-21}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n===Current===\n* Ahn Ji-young ([[Hangul]]: \uc548\uc9c0\uc601) \u2013 main vocals<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EC%95%88%EC%A7%80%EC%98%81&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=3490419|title=\uc548\uc9c0\uc601|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===Former===\n* Woo Ji-yoon ([[Hangul]]: \uc6b0\uc9c0\uc724) \u2013 guitar, bass, rapping, backing vocals<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&sm=tab_ppn&query=%EB%B3%BC%EB%B9%A8%EA%B0%84%EC%82%AC%EC%B6%98%EA%B8%B0&os=3490417&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService|title=\ubcfc\ube68\uac04\uc0ac\ucd98\uae30 \ud504\ub85c\ud544|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EC%9A%B0%EC%A7%80%EC%9C%A4&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=3490445|title=\uc6b0\uc9c0\uc724|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:25em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Gaon Album Chart|KOR]]<br /><ref>Gaon Album Chart:\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=40&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=Gaon Album Chart - Week 40 (Red Planet)|publisher=Gaon Music Chart|archivedate=2015-03-26|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Red Planet''\n|\n*Released: August 29, 2016\n*Label: Shofar Music\n*Formats: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]], [[streaming media|streaming]]\n{{hidden|Track listing|\n#'''Galaxy''' {{small|({{lang|ko|\uc6b0\uc8fc\ub97c \uc904\uac8c}})}}\n#Fight Day {{small|({{lang|ko|\uc2f8\uc6b4\ub0a0}})}}\n#You (<nowiki>=</nowiki>I)\n#Grumpy {{small|({{lang|ko|\uc2ec\uc220}})}}\n#'''Hard To Love''' {{small|({{lang|ko|\ub098\ub9cc \uc548\ub418\ub294 \uc5f0\uc560}})}}\n#Chocolate {{small|({{lang|ko|\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf}})}}\n#Freesia {{small|({{lang|ko|\ud504\ub9ac\uc9c0\uc544}})}}\n#X Song\n#Ring {{small|({{lang|ko|\ubc18\uc9c0}})}}\n#When You Fall In Love {{small|({{lang|ko|\uc0ac\ub791\uc5d0 \ube60\uc84c\uc744 \ub54c}})}}\n}}\n| 15\n|\n*KOR: 25,646<!--11,149 + 14,497--><ref>Cumulative sales of ''Red Planet'':\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=12&hitYear=2016&termGbn=month|title=2016\ub144 12\uc6d4 Album Chart}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=12&hitYear=2017&te